The quality profiles of the forward and reverse reads were plotted.

The gray scale in the plotâs background is the heat map of the frequency of each quality score at each position, with dark colors corresponding to a higher frequency.

The green line represents the mean quality score at each position.

The orange line represents the quartiles of the quality score distribution.

The red line shows the percentage of reads that extend to at least that position. illumina reads are generally the same length, therefore, the flat red line is at 100%.
